changelist.name: Create a new patient by posting an Xform instance
Move content provider to something that doesn't clash with ODK Collect
Send a form instance back to Open MRS.

task.summary: Refactor network calls for client app so they are switchable between Buendia server and OpenMSR server

I move the request queue to a static singleton as recommended here: http://developer.android.com/training/volley/requestqueue.html All network code is pulled out into the network package. I also add some ugly temporary code to convert to and from the Patient model.
This code works for adding a Person (not a patient yet) to the OpenMSR storage.

Incorporate ODK collect into project. I have stripped all references to Google maps and Google drive, but left most other things in.
I also haven't run the activity, I've just got everything so it compiles and the client still runs in the emulator.
I've also moved to the latest Gradle plugin - apologies if this forces you to update Android Studio.
Adding ODK collect that got missed in my last commit

Make ODK Collect FormEntryActivity work inside the Buendia Android app. Work in this case means load a form from the sdcard, and display it. The design for how to actually be provided with the form needs to be designed properly still. The code is triggered by changing a local binary variable in PatientListActivity, then pressing the scan button (to avoid having to add UI elements)
Do an RPC to Jon's OpenMRS module to get xforms. Working as a spike. Now have a String with xml in it.

Do an RPC to Jon's OpenMRS module to get xforms, and put them in the ODK storage. Currently doesn't work because of inconsistencies between XForms from OpenMRS and Xform expectations from openrosa. But does work locally if you have an OpenMRS server running locally with appropriate username/password.

Make XML parsing more lenient so OpenMRS forms actually work. Involves various hacky things that should be fixed on the server side, but we do now have a form being read from Jon's module, and being displayed.
Add code to list patients from OpenMrs using a new REST endpoint added in the Buendia module.
Work with the Project Buendia OpenMRS get an individual patient RPC
Put the ability to add an individual patient. Requires you to fill in the MSF Id.
Move content provider to something that doesn't clash with ODK Collect. Also add ACCESS_WIFI_STATE permission as it seemed to be needed by ODK collect.
Send a form instance back to Open MRS. Includes really ugly hardcoded form in constants, to be removed later.
